The paper discusses the development of a testing tool for a specific type of neural network, LSTMs. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) as it deals with the verification and validation of a software system. Additionally, the tool uses mutation-based test case generation, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for evaluating the robustness of models. The paper also discusses the use of LSTM networks for various sequential tasks, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the tool can help with the internal data flow processing of the LSTM layer, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
